    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD is a masterclass in lightweight engineering and high-revving performance. Under the hood, the 13B-REW rotary engine remains in its original sequential twin-turbocharged configuration, providing seamless boost transition across the power band. The chassis retains its factory 50/50 weight distribution, supported by a pristine double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for surgical turn-in precision. Every mechanical component, from the oil metering pump to the vacuum lines, has been meticulously maintained to ensure factory-spec operation. The exterior features original Montego Blue Mica paint with no clear-coat failure, while the interior remains a time capsule with zero bolster wear on the leather seats. Recent compression tests confirm the apex seals are well within optimal tolerances, making this a turn-key collector-grade specimen for the rotary purist.",
      "price": 46500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
